doc.content:
Maintain original message format
Telegram doesn't allow creating messages with extra spaces and new lines, instead it will trim all consecutive newlines or spaces into 1 newline and 1 space.
This is caused by using ```Html.fromHtml``` before handiling spaces and new lines also by code while typing the message:
```
String message = messsageEditText.getText().toString().trim();
message = message.replaceAll("\n\n+", "\n\n");
message = message.replaceAll(" +", " ");
```
This behavior sometimes breaks the message formatting specially if the message has ascii artwork or is arranged in special way.

The fix for this is easy:
* Remove the trimming of spaces and new lines (from ```onTextChanged```)
