Remove notification after you replied in different app
I often use my phone just for the notifications (and view media, if applicable) and use the CLI client on Linux to read and write messages. What happens is this:

1. Someone sends me a message;
2. The notification LED of my phone starts blinking;
3. I alt-tab on my laptop to the CLI client and read the message;
4. I reply;
5. The notification LED keeps blinking, even though I spoke last.

It would be great if the app could detect when the last incoming message was your own, and stop blinking the LED. It could also remove the notification in the notification area, but that's not as important to me.

The CLI client can also mark messages as read with the /read command, and it also automatically does this when you reply. I'm not sure whether the Android app receives these /read notifications from myself, but I'm sure it receives my own chat messages because they show up. Stopping the LED blinking upon receiving chat messages from myself surely works, but perhaps it could also stop blinking once it notices I /read the messages. This would be especially great since the Windows desktop client for Telegram seems to send /read automatically on window focus (not that I'd know, but a few contacts run Windows and it seems to do this).

Thanks!

